  "title" : "How to parse a JSON string into JsonNode in Jackson?",
  "body" : "<p>It should be so simple, but I just cannot find it after being trying for an hour.</p>\n<p>I need to get a JSON string, for example, <code>{&quot;k1&quot;:v1,&quot;k2&quot;:v2}</code>, parsed as a <code>JsonNode</code>.</p>\n<pre><code>JsonFactory factory = new JsonFactory();\nJsonParser jp = factory.createJsonParser(&quot;{\\&quot;k1\\&quot;:\\&quot;v1\\&quot;}&quot;);\nJsonNode actualObj = jp.readValueAsTree();\n</code></pre>\n<p>gives</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>java.lang.IllegalStateException: No ObjectCodec defined for the parser, can not deserialize JSON into JsonNode tree</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n"
}